This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it deals with discovering semantic frames from corpora. It also involves probabilistic modeling, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses inference issues, which could fall under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper analyzes syntactic parsing accuracy, which could fall under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
